23
00:01:03,730 --> 00:01:05,920
Independence usually describes
a situation where the

24
00:01:05,920 --> 00:01:09,360
occurrence or non-occurrence
of different events is

25
00:01:09,360 --> 00:01:13,170
determined by factors that
are completely unrelated.

26
00:01:13,170 --> 00:01:17,030
Independence is what allows us
to build complex models out of

27
00:01:17,030 --> 00:01:18,420
simple ones.

28
00:01:18,420 --> 00:01:21,640
This is because it is often the
case that a complex system

29
00:01:21,640 --> 00:01:24,640
is made up of several components
that are affected

30
00:01:24,640 --> 00:01:28,400
by unrelated, that is,
independent sources of

31
00:01:28,400 --> 00:01:29,960
randomness.

32
00:01:29,960 --> 00:01:33,300
And so with the tools to be
developed in this unit, we

33
00:01:33,300 --> 00:01:36,180
will be ready to calculate
probabilities in fairly

34
